  "prompt_text": "Design an end-of-life care planning tool. Address both the medical decision-making and the existential questions it raises.",
  "response_text": "**End-of-Life Care Planning Tool: Compassionate Pathways**\n\n**Medical Decision-Making Component:**\n\n1. **Assessment of Medical Status:**\n\t* Current health status (medical conditions, treatment options, prognosis)\n\t* Advance care planning (living will, power of attorney, Do Not Resuscitate (DNR) orders)\n2. **Goals of Care:**\n\t* Identify patient's values, preferences, and priorities\n\t* Discuss and agree on realistic goals of care (e.g., symptom management, comfort care, curative treatment)\n3. **Treatment Options:**\n\t* Review and discuss treatment options (e.g., palliative care, hospice, life-sustaining treatments)\n\t* Weigh benefits, risks, and burdens of each option\n4. **Decision-Making Roles:**\n\t* Identify decision-makers (patient, family, healthcare providers)\n\t* Clarify roles and responsibilities in decision-making\n\n**Existential Questions Component:**\n\n1. **Values and Meaning:**\n\t* Explore patient's values, beliefs, and worldview\n\t* Discuss the significance of life, purpose, and legacy\n2. **Life Review:**\n\t* Reflect on patient's life experiences, accomplishments, and relationships\n\t* Identify key themes, lessons learned, and regrets\n3. **Legacy and Impact:**\n\t* Explore how patient wants to be remembered and honored\n\t* Discuss ways to preserve legacy (e.g., donations, memorials, stories)\n4. **Spiritual and Emotional Support:**\n\t* Discuss patient's spiritual and emotional needs\n\t* Explore ways to provide comfort, support, and closure\n\n**Integrating Medical and Existential Components:**\n\n1. **Holistic Care Plan:**\n\t* Develop a comprehensive care plan that balances medical and existential needs\n\t* Incorporate patient's values, goals, and preferences\n2. **Communication and Support:**\n\t* Establish open communication among patient, family, and healthcare providers\n\t* Ensure ongoing support and care coordination\n3. **Review and Revision:**\n\t* Regularly review and revise the care plan as needed\n\t* Address changing needs, concerns, and priorities\n\n**Implementation and Follow-Up:**\n\n1. **Education and Training:**\n\t* Educate patient, family, and healthcare providers on end-of-life care\n\t* Provide resources and support for ongoing care\n2. **Monitoring and Evaluation:**\n\t* Regularly assess patient's needs and adjust the care plan accordingly\n\t* Evaluate the effectiveness of the care plan and make necessary changes\n3. **Emotional Support:**\n\t* Provide emotional support and counseling for patient, family, and healthcare providers\n\n**Compassionate Pathways Tool:**\n\nTo facilitate this process, a user-friendly tool can be created, including:\n\n1. A comprehensive assessment questionnaire to gather information on patient's medical status, values, and preferences\n2. A decision-making framework to guide",
